## 4. GraphQL Types (Inputs & Payloads)

Use `sealed record` for all input types and payload types. Use `required` on all mandatory properties.

```csharp
// Models/YourDomainInput.cs
public sealed record YourDomainInput
{
    [Required]
    [StringLength(100, MinimumLength = 1)]
    public required string Reference { get; init; }

    public required string SubmittedBy { get; init; }
}

// Models/YourDomainPayload.cs
public sealed record YourDomainPayload
{
    public required string Id { get; init; }
    public required string Reference { get; init; }
    public required string Status { get; init; }
    public required DateTimeOffset CreatedAt { get; init; }
}

// Models/YourDomainMutationPayload.cs
public sealed record YourDomainMutationPayload
{
    public YourDomainPayload? Record { get; init; }
    public IReadOnlyList<UserError> Errors { get; init; } = [];
}

public sealed record UserError
{
    public required string Message { get; init; }
    public required string Code { get; init; }
}
```

### Domain exceptions

```csharp
// Exceptions/YourDomainNotFoundException.cs
public sealed class YourDomainNotFoundException : Exception
{
    public string RecordId { get; }
    public YourDomainNotFoundException(string id) : base($"Record '{id}' was not found.")
        => RecordId = id;
}
```

