## 5. Resolver Patterns

Extend `Query.cs` and `Mutation.cs` — never add business logic directly in resolvers.

### Query resolver

```csharp
// Query.cs — extend the generated scaffold
[ExtendObjectType(OperationTypeNames.Query)]
public sealed class {{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}Query
{
    public async Task<YourDomainPayload> GetRecordAsync(
        string id,
        [Service] I{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }} service,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        return await service.GetAsync(id, cancellationToken);
    }

    [UsePaging]
    [UseFiltering]
    [UseSorting]
    public async Task<IQueryable<YourDomainPayload>> GetRecordsAsync(
        [Service] IYourDomainRepository repository,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        return repository.GetQueryable();
    }
}
```

### Mutation resolver

```csharp
// Mutation.cs — extend the generated scaffold
[ExtendObjectType(OperationTypeNames.Mutation)]
public sealed class {{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}Mutation
{
    public async Task<YourDomainMutationPayload> CreateRecordAsync(
        YourDomainInput input,
        [Service] I{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }} service,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        try
        {
            var result = await service.CreateAsync(input, cancellationToken);
            return new YourDomainMutationPayload { Record = result };
        }
        catch (YourDomainDuplicateException ex)
        {
            return new YourDomainMutationPayload
            {
                Errors = [new UserError { Message = ex.Message, Code = "DUPLICATE_REFERENCE" }]
            };
        }
    }

    public async Task<YourDomainMutationPayload> DeleteRecordAsync(
        string id,
        [Service] I{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }} service,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        try
        {
            await service.DeleteAsync(id, cancellationToken);
            return new YourDomainMutationPayload();
        }
        catch (YourDomainNotFoundException ex)
        {
            return new YourDomainMutationPayload
            {
                Errors = [new UserError { Message = ex.Message, Code = "NOT_FOUND" }]
            };
        }
    }
}
```

**Rules:**
- Resolvers only delegate to the service — no business logic inline
- Return mutation payload types with `Errors` collection — never throw from mutations
- Queries may throw `GraphQLException` for not-found — Hot Chocolate maps these to GraphQL errors

