## 10. Adding a New Feature — Step-by-Step

```
1. Define domain exceptions  →  Exceptions/YourDomainXxxException.cs
2. Add input/payload types   →  Models/XxxInput.cs, Models/XxxPayload.cs
3. Extend service interface  →  Services/I{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}.cs
4. Update entity + migration →  Data/YourDomainEntity.cs + dotnet ef migrations add
5. Implement repository      →  Data/YourDomainRepository.cs
6. Implement service method  →  Services/{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}Impl.cs (log + trace + metrics)
7. Add resolver              →  Query.cs or Mutation.cs
8. Write tests               →  Tests/Services/ + Tests/Resolvers/
9. Verify coverage           →  dotnet test --collect:"XPlat Code Coverage"
```

---

## 11. What NOT To Do

| Don't | Do instead |
|---|---|
| Put business logic in resolvers | Move it to `{{ model.names.dot_net_class_name }}` service |
| Throw exceptions from mutations | Return `UserError` in mutation payload |
| Use AutoMapper | Write explicit mapping methods |
| Call Genesis providers from resolvers | Go through the service |
| Use `.Result` or `.Wait()` | `await` all async calls |
| Log PII | Log IDs and operation names only |
| Add NuGet packages without approval | Raise a ticket per `DEPENDENCY_MANAGEMENT.md` |
| Modify `Program.cs` | Raise a Pervaxis platform ticket |
| Skip tests | 90% coverage is a CI gate |

